1
00:00:09,785 --> 00:00:11,988
[I miss you, Hyun Jae. Don't you miss me?]

2
00:00:19,675 --> 00:00:23,704
[Delete this message]

3
00:00:25,987 --> 00:00:29,027
Personal phones are prohibited from now on.

4
00:00:29,027 --> 00:00:31,714
If you need a phone,
ask your manager for permission.

5
00:00:31,714 --> 00:00:34,067
You will then use the communal phone.

6
00:00:34,067 --> 00:00:35,507
What, really?

7
00:00:35,507 --> 00:00:39,121
Yes. We've already arranged with your agencies.

8
00:00:40,041 --> 00:00:42,541
But this is too sudden.

9
00:00:44,194 --> 00:00:48,441
I know you've been through a lot.

10
00:00:49,334 --> 00:00:51,016
But...

11
00:00:51,700 --> 00:00:53,887
we can't allow personal mistakes

12
00:00:53,887 --> 00:00:57,325
to interfere with others' hard work.

13
00:00:57,325 --> 00:00:58,672
Not only that,

14
00:00:58,672 --> 00:01:01,965
but the agency,
which is putting all their trust in you,

15
00:01:01,965 --> 00:01:04,518
family, and your fans.

16
00:01:05,212 --> 00:01:08,665
You wouldn't want to trouble them, would you?

17
00:01:08,665 --> 00:01:11,465
We'd appreciate your cooperation.

18
00:01:12,758 --> 00:01:14,812
Are we clear?

19
00:01:38,352 --> 00:01:40,605
<i>Do you really have no feelings for me?</i>

20
00:02:14,176 --> 00:02:15,733
What?

21
00:02:17,384 --> 00:02:19,384
<i>Dangerous...</i>

22
00:02:20,278 --> 00:02:22,245
<i>You!</i>

23
00:02:22,245 --> 00:02:24,245
<i>You're dangerous.</i>

24
00:02:25,187 --> 00:02:28,625
<i>Pay you back with my body?</i>

25
00:02:28,625 --> 00:02:31,358
<i>Usually, I'd just swear you out.</i>

26
00:02:31,358 --> 00:02:32,912
<i>Bam!</i>

27
00:02:35,012 --> 00:02:36,568
<i>That's what I'd do.</i>

28
00:02:46,325 --> 00:02:48,392
<i>Or else, people would...</i>

29
00:02:48,392 --> 00:02:50,598
<i>get the wrong idea.</i>

30
00:03:02,891 --> 00:03:05,936
I can't believe myself!

31
00:03:11,984 --> 00:03:13,664
Darn it!

32
00:03:15,529 --> 00:03:17,633
This can't be!

33
00:03:17,633 --> 00:03:19,324
It was just a few shots of soju!

34
00:03:19,324 --> 00:03:21,644
Why can't I remember anything?

35
00:03:22,971 --> 00:03:24,304
[Exploring Relationships]

36
00:03:24,304 --> 00:03:26,834
[Make teams of two to get to know each other]
In this class, you will pair in twos,

37
00:03:26,834 --> 00:03:29,924
and present on the partnership.

38
00:03:29,924 --> 00:03:32,924
We finished teaming up last week.

39
00:03:34,777 --> 00:03:37,831
The course adjustment period ends today, right?

40
00:03:37,831 --> 00:03:40,111
Who's our newest addition?

41
00:03:40,111 --> 00:03:43,357
Oh, I'm Shin Jae Min.

42
00:03:45,017 --> 00:03:47,822
We already made teams during orientation.

43
00:03:47,822 --> 00:03:49,091
What now?

44
00:03:49,091 --> 00:03:53,962
Is there anyone who would like
to operate as a team of three?

45
00:03:55,171 --> 00:03:57,997
Shin Jae Min? Isn't he from that show?

46
00:03:57,997 --> 00:04:01,909
Didn't he have some sort of controversy?

47
00:04:01,909 --> 00:04:03,824
He's that stalker, right?

48
00:04:03,824 --> 00:04:06,271
Stalker? Where?

49
00:04:08,164 --> 00:04:09,757
I'll do it.

50
00:04:12,784 --> 00:04:14,097
I'll team up with him.

51
00:04:14,097 --> 00:04:15,824
Oh, Mr. Khun.

52
00:04:15,824 --> 00:04:19,017
You signed up from the language center, right?

53
00:04:19,017 --> 00:04:22,316
Perfect, the two of you can team up.

54
00:05:30,897 --> 00:05:33,495
[Sorry, my legs are too long]

55
00:06:05,924 --> 00:06:07,747
Excuse me.

56
00:06:08,702 --> 00:06:11,777
- Is that Kim Hyun Jae?
- Kim Hyun Jae?

57
00:06:11,777 --> 00:06:13,647
I think so.

58
00:06:27,377 --> 00:06:29,306
Go home. Right now.

59
00:06:29,306 --> 00:06:30,628
Can we talk?

60
00:06:30,628 --> 00:06:32,717
There's nothing to talk about.

61
00:06:32,717 --> 00:06:34,381
Will you be here tomorrow?

62
00:06:36,651 --> 00:06:38,031
Why are you doing this?

63
00:06:38,031 --> 00:06:39,751
Why do you keep showing up?

64
00:06:39,751 --> 00:06:42,751
- I'm here to study.
- Nonsense.

65
00:06:47,664 --> 00:06:48,817
I missed you.

66
00:06:48,817 --> 00:06:50,599
Missed me?

67
00:06:53,731 --> 00:06:56,004
You have it easy, don't you?

68
00:06:57,531 --> 00:06:59,751
You just act on your whims.

69
00:06:59,751 --> 00:07:01,331
Who do you think you are?

70
00:07:01,331 --> 00:07:04,771
- Do I look like some pushover?
- Can you not be difficult for once?

71
00:07:04,771 --> 00:07:06,068
What?

72
00:07:06,677 --> 00:07:08,704
Can't you smile for me?

73
00:07:08,704 --> 00:07:10,564
Say hi, stuff like that.

74
00:07:10,564 --> 00:07:12,337
- Why would I do that?
- Why are you so cruel to me?

75
00:07:12,337 --> 00:07:14,040
Kim Hyun Jae!

76
00:07:14,944 --> 00:07:16,437
The show's over.

77
00:07:16,437 --> 00:07:18,371
We're nothing. Nothing at all.

78
00:07:18,371 --> 00:07:20,384
Wasn't it enough, using each other for fame?

79
00:07:20,384 --> 00:07:23,017
What more is there? Oh, I see.

80
00:07:23,731 --> 00:07:25,884
Want me to sleep with you?

81
00:07:30,097 --> 00:07:32,211
If not, leave me alone.

82
00:07:33,245 --> 00:07:35,665
I don't want to see you ever again.

83
00:07:37,894 --> 00:07:39,386
Okay.

84
00:07:40,061 --> 00:07:42,527
If you want it that badly.

85
00:07:42,527 --> 00:07:44,614
Let's never cross paths again.

86
00:08:01,081 --> 00:08:02,925
Did you sleep well?

87
00:08:04,981 --> 00:08:06,629
You...

88
00:08:12,141 --> 00:08:15,367
Now, are you seated in teams?

89
00:08:15,367 --> 00:08:17,714
Let's move on to the lesson.

90
00:08:17,714 --> 00:08:19,927
Yesterday, I...

91
00:08:19,927 --> 00:08:22,861
I didn't say anything weird,

92
00:08:22,861 --> 00:08:24,881
or make any mistakes...

93
00:08:24,881 --> 00:08:26,414
did I?

94
00:08:26,414 --> 00:08:28,414
Mistake.

95
00:08:33,547 --> 00:08:35,501
Did I, like, say weird stuff?

96
00:08:35,501 --> 00:08:36,907
I don't know.

97
00:08:36,907 --> 00:08:38,447
I can't speak Korean.

98
00:08:38,447 --> 00:08:41,447
Wow, playing that card, huh?

99
00:08:43,774 --> 00:08:47,027
Nowadays, personal choices and beliefs...

100
00:08:47,027 --> 00:08:49,241
Are we a...

101
00:08:49,241 --> 00:08:50,387
couple?

102
00:08:50,387 --> 00:08:52,306
Couple?

103
00:08:52,306 --> 00:08:54,534
Now, you will pretend to be married...

104
00:08:54,534 --> 00:08:57,081
to your partner in class.

105
00:08:57,081 --> 00:08:59,367
Then, shall we learn about couples, lovers,

106
00:08:59,367 --> 00:09:02,370
and their relationship to marriage?

107
00:09:02,370 --> 00:09:04,334
[Starting point of marriage: Couple]
A couple is when two people

108
00:09:04,334 --> 00:09:05,965
maintain a close relationship

109
00:09:05,965 --> 00:09:07,172
- Oh.
- emotionally, sexually,

110
00:09:07,172 --> 00:09:09,463
and economically.

111
00:09:10,321 --> 00:09:13,307
Now, let's get to know each other better.

112
00:09:13,307 --> 00:09:15,347
Keep a close eye on your partner.

113
00:09:15,347 --> 00:09:18,587
Find out what they like, and don't like.

114
00:09:21,561 --> 00:09:23,394
So, what do you like, Khun?

115
00:09:23,394 --> 00:09:25,072
Favorite.

116
00:09:26,881 --> 00:09:29,147
You know, Jae Min.

117
00:09:29,147 --> 00:09:30,171
What?

118
00:09:30,171 --> 00:09:33,647
Yesterday, we already showed each other.

119
00:09:33,647 --> 00:09:35,360
Didn't we?

120
00:09:36,441 --> 00:09:38,501
What you're good at...

121
00:09:39,661 --> 00:09:41,074
and what you like.

122
00:09:41,074 --> 00:09:42,718
What?

123
00:09:43,587 --> 00:09:44,687
Jae Min.

124
00:09:44,687 --> 00:09:47,601
Do you have any questions?

125
00:09:47,601 --> 00:09:49,058
No, ma'am.

126
00:09:58,481 --> 00:10:00,747
When did he even stop by?

127
00:10:00,747 --> 00:10:03,014
Acting like he owns the place.

128
00:10:09,841 --> 00:10:12,114
Ah, what the hell!

129
00:10:12,114 --> 00:10:15,514
- Hi.
- What are you doing at my place?

130
00:10:15,514 --> 00:10:17,816
Never mind.

131
00:10:17,816 --> 00:10:19,410
Hey, you're drunk.

132
00:10:19,410 --> 00:10:21,315
Is everything okay?

133
00:10:22,676 --> 00:10:24,196
Anyway.

134
00:10:24,196 --> 00:10:25,796
What got into you? You spent the night out.

135
00:10:25,796 --> 00:10:27,210
Huh?

136
00:10:27,210 --> 00:10:29,028
You're in yesterday's clothes.

137
00:10:29,643 --> 00:10:31,896
What's it to you?

138
00:10:32,750 --> 00:10:35,376
Do you have it going with someone?

139
00:10:35,376 --> 00:10:37,400
I can't tell if it's going well...

140
00:10:37,400 --> 00:10:38,923
or badly.

141
00:10:38,923 --> 00:10:42,056
Well, you slept over. I'd say that's good.

142
00:10:42,056 --> 00:10:43,844
Good for you.

143
00:10:44,656 --> 00:10:46,879
Meanwhile, I'm doomed.

144
00:10:47,523 --> 00:10:49,543
What do you mean?

145
00:10:50,903 --> 00:10:53,492
Hey, did you bump into Soo An or what?

146
00:10:58,650 --> 00:11:01,436
Hey, are you crying?

147
00:11:01,436 --> 00:11:03,651
Hey, talk to me!

148
00:11:04,390 --> 00:11:05,849
Hey!

149
00:11:06,436 --> 00:11:09,372
[Manager]

150
00:11:12,670 --> 00:11:15,028
Hey, it's from work. Take it.

151
00:11:23,256 --> 00:11:25,763
[Unicorn Yung Jun]

152
00:11:25,763 --> 00:11:27,876
A merger?

153
00:11:27,876 --> 00:11:29,876
With Unicorn?

154
00:11:31,050 --> 00:11:32,150
<i>That's right.</i>

155
00:11:32,150 --> 00:11:33,910
<i>You'd know, too.</i>

156
00:11:33,910 --> 00:11:35,564
<i>It's Soo An's agency.</i>

157
00:11:39,016 --> 00:11:41,463
Who would've guessed?

158
00:11:41,463 --> 00:11:44,330
Aren't Soo An and Hyun Jae
supposed to be really close?

159
00:11:44,330 --> 00:11:45,743
No, stop being rude.

160
00:11:45,743 --> 00:11:46,996
Hello.

161
00:11:46,996 --> 00:11:48,290
But that's too far!

162
00:11:48,290 --> 00:11:50,496
What a soulless jerk.

163
00:11:51,316 --> 00:11:52,410
Good, you're here.

164
00:11:52,410 --> 00:11:55,673
Why did you bring me back as a trainee?

165
00:11:55,673 --> 00:11:57,923
I just don't get it.

166
00:12:00,310 --> 00:12:02,443
The company needs you.

167
00:12:06,870 --> 00:12:08,735
What's he doing here?

